column6: These were my first pair of Lulu leggings that I bought and I absolutely love them! In fact I enjoyed them so much that I recently bought a second pair because they were getting so much use. The waistband is awesome and it stays high throughout yoga flows and workouts which was a must for me. The length of the pant is perfect and I enjoy the little bit of ventilation from the mesh up the leg. Overall, I would definitely suggest this purchase.

I got these pants a month ago and they somehow ripped a hole in the back (I did not snag it on anything). They're very cute and flattering, but not good quality for the price. A $100 pair of leggings should not have a hole within one month of purchasing. Disappointing.

column6: The Train Times legging are quickly moving to the top of my list for my favorite pants. These are great for running and HIIT workouts as they don't don't fall or roll down. The mesh detail at the bottom gives the pant a little flair on an otherwise simple pant.
I loved the fit of these pants. They are sliming, but it is still easy to move! I got my normal size.

I love the train times pants and crops. I have a few pairs and love them. They stay put, are super comfortable, and great for running, lifting, or orangetheory classes. I picked up a pair in we are from space in white/grey when i found them in store for final sale. I didn't try them on because I already own the same style and know my size in these. Big mistake! The white/grey totally fails the squat test. I'm glad I checked at home, before wearing them out, but am totally disappointed with this pair.

column6: These are great! They are a very tight fit and never find myself pulling them up during any practice, even my more intense sculpt practices these never move and have not pilled like my Wunder unders. Highly recommend. Also very flattering!

I am 5'4" and weigh 130 with an athletic build. I bought a size 8 and 6. The size 8 was too big but the size 6 is perfect. No tugging on the waistline all day, they stay in place and look so flattering and have a nice tummy control area. I bought in 2 colors Olive and Black...and may need more!

These are my absolute favorite pair of lulu leggings! The 7/8s length is perfect for my height and they are very flattering. I have worn and washed them 3 times with no signs of wear and tear. I even bought two more pairs. Very true to size. For reference, I am 5'5", 140 pounds with an athletic build and I wear a size 6 which fits perfectly. Highly recommend!

These are my fav fit of lulu’s. I have the black & olive colors. I get so many compliments on the cute mesh detail. I’ve had the olive pair for a few months now and the mesh is a very high quality that hasn’t snagged or ripped even though I wear these to death. The material sucks you in & hugs in all the right places without feeling constricted. love love love.

I have the train times in the pant and in the 21" crop and these are my favorite leggings. I love the snug fit in the waist, they're squat proof, and so comfortable. I use them for cross training, strength training, barre, and boot camp style classes... so basically everything.

column5: Wanted to give a 5 star, but...
column6: I love ALL Lululemon product, but the white train pants are not a good idea. I have worn them once and the pants have discolored within one wash. Does not appear to be the fresh white that I purchased. I'm very disappointed because I have only worn them once and I've never had this problem with other colors before (and let me tell you, I buy A LOT of Lulu). I'm familiar with the Lululemon wash procedure so not sure why this happened? I suggest you buy ANY color in these pants but WHITE.
column14: i love the fit of the pants
column15: the white changes color within one wash

column6: I LOVE these leggings so much that I'm reviewing them. I have several other pairs of lulus including wunder unders, and a speed up tight. These fit SO well and don't slide down like the others do. I do cross fit 3x and run 4-10 miles 2x a week. I strictly use my leggings for working out. There's no sign of pilling or ripping at all (though I've had them since December), but they get washed very frequently and have gone through a ton of washing already (unlike my wunder unders that are pilling, but I've had those for a couple of years). Now that I absolutely found my favorite legging I will have to buy more. The drawstring is definitely my favorite part because it helps keep the pants in place. I would have to say that these leggings are an excellent choice for people who are serious about their training. I'm 5'2 and weight 114 and have an athletic body -- I wear a size 4 in these.
column15: back pocket should be a front pocket

column6: I wish I could've given 0 stars instead of 1. I was extremely disappointed in these pants. The pants were very thin and were not flattering at all. They were also very see through and I could literally see my underwear when I bent over to tie my shoe. They did nothing to smooth any bumps or dimples in my butt or legs. The only thing I liked was the heathered charcoal color I ordered. I had to send them back and would not recommend them to a friend.

I have been searching for the best pair of black leggings for inside and outside of the gym. I am obsessed with the full-on luxtreme. This fabric is incredible. IT DOES NOT SHOW SWEAT. I always have an issue with sweat showing through my leggings during intense workouts, but with these, thats not the case. These leggings make your legs and butt look incredible, and they are SO comfortable. They do run a little small, however. I am usually a size 4 in lulu's, but I had to size up to a 6 in these leggings. My only complaint is that I noticed a little bit of pilling on the sides and back on the seams. GET THESE LEGGINGS. You will not regret it. Also LULU PLEASE make these in navy blue and restock in both grey colors!!! I want to order another pair ASAP!

I own at least 15 pairs of Lululemon leggings and these are by far my favorite. I've worn them 4-5 times now and they have kept their shape. Super flattering fit, buttery soft fabric that moves with you, and a great length (they end right above my ankles and I'm 5'9). Best part is that you can't see sweat through these! I got the Gatsby Blue color and was worried about that, but these passed the test through both a treadmill workout and an intense 1 hour HIIT circuit class. Will buy other colors!

I have the exact same version of this pants in two colors both in the same size, but for some reason, the material of the white ones I bought more recently seems to be different. They are so much tighter even after a couple of washes, they are still tight to put on. It's a bit confusing because the other pair I own fit me perfectly. Really disappointed because I really love the original ones and want to own one in white..
I am absolutely in love with these pants, they fit so well, but they wearing off at the seams. I am so heartbroken that I paid so much and now they are tearing up. Wish they could do better jpb.
column15: wearing off at the seams after couple of wears

column6: Finally found my go-to tights for all my workouts, from CrossFit to running to cycling, Body Pump classes, weight lifting, rope climbing, walking around the neighborhood, these pants don't disappoint. They stay on and stay up.
These pants fit great and are easy to work out in, but the material has an odor that even after washing hasn't helped. Disappointing because I loved the color.

column6: Love the Red color, fit, and soft material.

I ordinarily love Lulu leggings but this might be my first disappointment. They smell toxic out and after a couple washes they still have a plastic odor. The description sounded amazing, but these didn’t quite make the cut.

column6: I have been wearing Lululemon since I was in high school. I got these pant and fell in love with the design and fit. They look great and don't fall when I run. Unfortunately, the seams on my pants have slowly one by one been snagging off. The pants are great but I have seen the quality in Lululemon decrease over the years. Really sad since I did love them.

column6: I've finally found a pair of tights that fit me well. I walk a lot outside and on the treadmill and take barre classes regularly. These stay in place throughout barre class through all the movements and positions, so I'm excited about that. They seem to be durable enough so far from a washing standpoint. They provide me with a very clean line and I feel great when I wear them.
Very good compression. That stay in place when I lift at the gym

column5: Luxtreme remains my fav!!! Always comfy and flattering.
column6: I only wear luxtreme tights. They are great for running and pure barre and I like the silky/buttery feeling better than any other lulu fabric. I highly recommend these.
Love how these stay up during HIIT workouts. Just wish they had the side pockets. I also love the floral pattern. I need more of these!

I absolutely love these leggings. They are so cute and great for working out. I have four different pairs because I love them so much! They stay up really well and really hold everything in, so they are great for working out. If you are trying to decide on what leggings to get, definitely get these!!!

I had been concerned that as soon as I got one pair of lulu leggings that I was going to need to change over all of my leggings, and I was right. These leggings move with you whether you’re in the grocery store or Orangetheory, they are simply the best and I’m not sure how to where something else now.

Great legging for high intensity workouts. Only complaint is the waist line. Mine do roll down anytime I bend over at the waist. My fast and free with a higher waist do not roll down so I will buy those in the future but these are still great.
The leggings I got fit very well and I love the material
column14: i loved the smoothness of the leggings

column6: I got the full length pant in June of 2018 and hadn’t worn them over the summer and just recently found them in my drawer they have become my favorite pants !! Please don’t discontinue I noticed when I was in the store last week they weren’t available only the 7/8 online.

These are the BEST workout pants I've ever had. I have them in 3 colors and will keep buying them until they stop making them. The 7/8 is the perfect length and I love the look of the mesh panels on the calves. The pockets are roomy enough for keys and other essentials and the drawstring makes them my go-to choice for running, bootcamp, HIIT and other intense workouts. I also wear them to pilates and for life in general b/c they're so comfortable and smooth. Wore my first pair for a 24 hour travel day from the US to India last year- that's how comfortable they are.
column15: they don't stock them at my local store anymore :(

column6: So comfortable! I wear them all the time

I love these pants! Their fit is so flattering and the material is perfect for training and Pilates. I only wish they had an option without the mesh on the lower leg. Then I would buy one in every color!

I didn't hate or like these pants very much. I agree with many of the comments, the mesh is fun. However, it's truly annoying how often these pants fall down when I am working out, even despite the drawstring. Can't really run in them or jump or do anything higher intensity. They aren't even that great for my lifting days. I will admit they are cute, but not functional for me. The length is nice and they feel like butter, so I guess that's good.

column6: I got these because I love my older pair so much that I wore them till they were coming apart. They don’t sell the exact ones anymore but these are similar. They gave me these as a replacement and they are great!

I own three pair of these. Two pairs I bought almost a year ago (black and grey) and another black pair just now. They feel snug and are very flattering, even after wearing and washing at least 50 times. They stay put during HIIT workouts and jogging. I will warn against ordering the grey color. It does show every drop of sweat. I reserve those for home workouts because when im done exercising it looks like I peed myself :< Buy them in black!
I got these in a red color and they are stunning. The fit is great, and they are so comfortable to work out in. I love them!

column5: Love them, Run a little small!
column6: I really like these! They are very slimming, nice and smoothing. I'm between a 4 and a 6, usually and I got these in a 4 to have more compression. They fit, but they are definitely tight! I have a small waist, and 6s often are too loose around it. So even though they are a bit tight, I don't think I would trade for a 6. For reference, I am 5' 4" (perfect ankle length on me) roughly 125-130lbs, with a decent sized rump.

column5: great pant, but the luminosity fades very quickly
column6: I love this style and fit, the problem is mine were the luminosity foil print in black/silver and after less than 10 wears they have faded drastically and now I cannot wear them since they have faded in alot of places and looks very uneven. I have only washed a couple times inside out and with cold and air dry. I have another pair in dark teal and they wear amazing and have not faded at all, I am just unhappy with the silver luminosity ones.

column6:
5'3". 25" is full length for me. Good fit on ankles. Mesh cut out on bottom holds me in with no issues. Waistband occasionally rolls down during workout but not enough to be irritating.
125 to 130 pounds. Size 6. Perfect fit.
Bought black. No sweatmarks seen. Not sheer. Medium compression. Speed up tight is more tight. No side pockets. Only back pocket.
Would love to get with print.
Keeps me warm in california winters. Sweat wicking. Able to move around and do all my stretches and strength training.
Train times are my go to lulu purchase. I have tons of pairs. But my last 4 pairs the material is not the same and semi see tru. Not super impressed with these last pairs.
I love these!!! Feel amazing and still hold me close! Perfect pant for hard workouts!

Stylish, and they have a great fit. The mesh is super cute. The only problem I had was that I ordered my normal size, washed them per their instructions, and they were super tight the last time I put them on. I ordered my normal size and the size up and returned the size up because it was too big, but I should have kept the bigger size.

I have 3 pairs of these pants and I truly do love them. I have the heathered black, gatsby blue, and figue. These pants are the perfect length, they look beautiful, fit like a glove, and they are comfortable and move with you when training. My only complaint is that I've had the heathered black pants for just shy of 9 months now and the fabric and stitches of the inner thigh is wearing a lot that I fear if I wear them during a workout, they will rip/pop open and I will be in an embarrasing situation. Basically, long term quality is failing and my one pair I cannot wear due to the wear and coming apart in the inner thigh area.
column19: {'LL_response_content': "Dear Nic13,\n\nThank you for taking the time to share your feedback with us. I'm sorry to hear that the Train Times 7/8 Pant is not performing for you. Keep an eye out for an email coming your way. Chat soon!", 'LL_response_date': 'January 5, 2019'}

column6: I’m 5’5” and have relatively short legs. The full length leggings from lulu are too long for me, so I usually opt for the cropped. I tried the 7/8 leggings, and they fit perfectly on my legs! So if you’re short/have short legs and are looking for a full length legging, go with these! The side panels with mesh is so cute. Would definitely reccomend.

column5: Great pants, possibly meant for narrow hips.
column6: I typically wear Wunder Under Hi-Rise for workouts, but I needed something that didn't need to be pulled up every two seconds. These are definitely fit for the job! I wear size 4 in all bottoms and these are a struggle to put on because the waist is so narrow. Unfortunately, I've already torn the seam (in the three different places) at the waist. I do love the idea of this design. I just don't think the waist is flexible enough? Either way, I recommend it if you need something that will stay in place during workouts.

These are my absolute favorite leggings. They fit pretty tight, but they are amazing. If you don't like really compressed leggings, maybe size up. However, I got my usual size and I love them! I use them for every day from running to going to work/class.
Love these pants. They're great. Highly recommend!
Fits smaller than average but molds to your figure with time. Love the design—it’s the fourth TrainTimes for me!

I love these pants! I have two- one in the army green & one in black! I'm normally size 0-1 in my normal every day jeans/pants/slacks, however, for this legging, I chose a size 4. They hug in just the right places. I just use the band to make it tighter, and it fits me well! I really love working out in these or even just wearing them on casual days. The material and fit is worth the price!

Love the detail of these pants but I’ve washed only 1 time so far and the seems are fraying already. I’m an avid lulu lover and this was a pair I would not recommend for those who are active love to workout and on the go. Its too bad because they looked good.

column6: It fits perfectly all over . It does not fall down. I can be in it all day! Love it.

column5: Everytime I wear these, I wonder why I don't have more!
column6:
These tights fit so great, are just the right weight and stylish to boot! What more could you ask for? You must try them. They are good for cardio, strength training anything.
They hug you in, but not too tight, just the right length... love the mesh detail, high enough waist, the weight of the material is just right. Not too heavy.
Please Lulu, please don't discontinue... My store does not carry them in stock anymore.... should I be worried??? Please say no!

These things are durable!! Let me tell you a story. This evening I was running from the parking lot to my house, and you know those videos where someone trips and they run a little bit while they’re slowly falling over, their arms flail and then they slide across the ground as they fall? Oh and whatever is in their hands flies out of them? Yep. That was me tonight. Literally... I feel right onto a cement sidewalk and it hurt so bad. I got up and limped back inside. I was SURE I ruined my leggings. Nope! There was not a tear to be seen on them! I looked all over the entire pant and there was not a scrape. But SOMEHOW my knee got tore to shreds! Idk how my knee got tore up but the leggings stayed perfectly in tact, but they did, and that is why I am writing such an awesome review. So if you're clumsy like me, you HAVE to try these! They will not disappoint.
I have to add too, the style is super nice, I love the mesh detailing up the sides as well! They fit very well, snug, but not so snug they are uncomfortable!
I highly recommend these pants if you sweat ALOT at the gym. They’re also comfortable when doing lots of movement. I hope they never discontinue this style!

These are my first pair of Lululemon leggings and they look and feel great! I ordered these online in the dark olive color and it was true to color in person. I am 5'3 and hover between 126-131 lbs and got a size 6. They fit comfortably and provide decent compression for weight training. Only criticism is that I am on the shorter side and these don't quite fit like a capri on me like they do for the tall models in the photos...its more like an awkward high-water length so I roll up the hems.

LOVE LOVE LOVE these leggings! I bought the red which is more brick red than a true dark red and that would be the ONLY negative comment I have to say about these tights. They have compression and are a little thicker which is fantastic for Boot Camp/CrossFit and regular old school lifting. They are a perfect choice to workout in during the winter months. I will admit I have worn them for 2 non consecutive days hit Crossfit, hiked with my dogs and then to the gym with out washing and they stay put and haven't stretched nor o they smell....I have NEVER done that with workout gear before... Buy them you will love them! I plan to buy more!

Love the train times style. It works especially well when running, weight training, high impact exercises. No shifting or adjusting...unlike my wonder under, and align styles—which those are perfect for yoga, lounge, etc.

I loved these leggings from the moment I tried them on. Ive had them a few months now and I can no longer wear them. The hip seam on the left frayed so much that when I took them out of the washer, on delicate cycle, they frame had turned into a hole. I was so heart broken because these were my first white leggings, and instead of stains being my probably it was the actual material itself. I can't exchange them now or I would 100%!

column6: They hug nicely and I like the mesh along the calves. A pretty touch. They allow me to move as advertised and this is important. I didn't give 5 stars as they wrinkle behind my knees.

These are by far my favorite pants! I have about 6 pair! I occasionally try other leggings, but always come back to my train times! I love the compression they offer and that they stay up and also have a draw string when I need it!

I love these tights. I own three pairs and will continue to add to my collection. I'm 5'4 120 and wear these in size 4 (my usual size). They have the perfect amount of compression and hold me in exactly where I need them to. They make my legs look long and toned. They are perfect for bootcamp but they also work well for lower impact workouts. They don't show sweat, they don't restrict movement, they stay put, and they look fantastic.

column5: Good at first, then turned bad
column6: I loved these pants at first! They hugged my body amazingly then after about 5 washes, they completely lost all of the hugging sensation and the waist band began to roll over every time I sat down. I would constantly have to adjust them whenever I work out. I won't be buying these again.

I really loved these train time pants when I first bought them, but after 4 wears and washes the waistband is very relaxed and rolls down during my practice. column6: I can't believe all the negative reviews. I have had these pants for 1 year now and they are in great shape and have been used 1x per week for workout classes. They are the absolute BEST lululemon work out pants I own as the waistband really stays put for burpees, mountain climbers, etc. Wonderunders always slide down for me during those types of activities. I recently went into a lululemon store to buy more-only to find out that they are online only. Please bring back to stores and in more colors!

I actually really love these leggings, I was hesitant at first given some reviews but I have yet to have an issue with these. I love how they aren't made from a super thin material, they are not too thick but just right. They don't ride up when while I work out. They are perfect. I would buy more if I had the budget

Traditionally I have loved those pants and have purchased them in a five different colors. When I purchased them in the dark pink I noticed that the stiching at the seams is starting to unravel and I've owned them less than a month. I only ever air dry them. Truly disappointed in the quality.

column6: I am ultra picky when it comes to leggings- If I am going to have something skintight...it better look good! These pants deliver! The perfect high waist and seams along the leg are very flattering. Not to mention, they are actually functional! Have about 4 pairs- I tend to go for the darker colors, the texture is a little thicker and "holds you in" a tad more.

column5: Cute, but the fabric isn't super comfortable
column6: If you want great fabric, try the speed up tight. These are good, fabric is forgiving, but just not as comfortable as I expect from lulu. I bought an 8 (5/7" and 145/heavy on top) and they were small. I'd need a 10. Boo.

I love Lulu's Full on Luxtreme fabric, but it doesn't work for this pants. My normal size is 6 for Align and 8 for Speed up. I bought an 8. I think it should be my right size, while it become loose just after 4 or 5 washes. After first running in this pants, I found it left a mark of the seam on my calf. It's tight, it even cut off circulation when seating in this pants. I use it for running so the cut it's okay, but now the pants stretched out a lot. The calf part is finally comfortable but the crotch part looks really baggy. I didn't gain weight so I'm really confused how could it stretched out so fast. Now every time I see this pants I feel sad for the money I paid.

column6: Good fit esp for my small frame (5'3, 100 lbs) and not too long. True to size. Hugs well. Material nice.
column14: fitted material nice doesn't collect lint

column6: I like the fit but the pattern stretches! The color I got (Shorelines Multi Blue/Black) is lined with WHITE fabric so even the slightest pull makes the pattern look stretched out. I had a friend who is much smaller than me try them on and they even looked stretched on her. I also have the heather grey color and those aren't lined but are see through as some mentioned in other reviews. Very disappointed! At this price point none of these patterns should look stretched out and no pants should be see through!

The best leggings. Sucks everything in and very flattering.

These leggings fit great (in fact a little tight) on the first try but have loosened up around the waist significantly over 4-5 wears despite following wash/dry instructions and need constant pulling up in the gym...not fun while in the middle of squats. I wish the form would've held up better for the price paid; now wishing I would've been made aware of the tendency for these to open up and maybe I would've sized down while purchasing.

column6:
i have at least 20 lulu pants and this one's my new favorite!
it's tight enough to hold in and loosen enough to do yoga.
i do both gym workouts and yoga and it's perfect for both.
usually wear size 2-4 in lulu and 4 fits perfect.

The Train Times pants felt like wearing a wetsuit. I got my normal size in lulu...sizing up would’ve been bad and sizing down would’ve been bad. Really couldn’t win with these ones and I didn’t feel they were worth the money at all. I have a pair of pants that look identical from Old Navy that are full compression without wet suit detailing. Returned these immediately.
Love the material & surprised I could actually get away with wearing white bottoms.

These are my new favorite workout pant. They have a good compression and the high waist is comfortable and flattering. I always have trouble with pants riding down during a workout and these actually stay up during crossfit WODs and running. My waist is quite smaller than my butt and hips so sizing is hard for me, but an 8 in these are perfect. In order to get pants that don't ride down I have to size down to a 6 in Lulu sometimes. I'm 5'9" and the 7/8 is a great length.

column5: Website Picture is different than actual item.
column6: The pants themselves are great, but what I ordered online shows Heather Grey pants with a Black Waistband and Accents. The pants I received are all Grey, not sure how that happened but it's disappointing because I would not have ordered all grey pants.

i've never had any issues of sweat marks show on any of my workout pants from other brands, but my oh my do these pants show them like no other —in embarrassing areas at that. wanted to love these pants so much given they are my first pair of lulus. better luck next time.

I bought it in 2 colors: a black one from lulu store in Boston ( i exchanged for another one that i bought online) and a grey one though here.
I' petite , size 2: the grey is perfect , the black is loose especially in th ankles, i think because the net is no thin ( in the grey is ticker material ) . Even the waistband in the black after use it 2 times got really loose , I.m new in USA, I've been use lulu form the past 8 years in Australia, and i think they loosing quality.
These fit my waist in a way none of my other leggings have in the past. I love the compressed feel on my legs and the overall quality of the material of this legging.

column5: Love the Length and the Hugged Sensation
column6: The hugged sensation feels just right, enough to hold in the jiggles, but does not feel at all suffocating. I'm wearing these leggings to everything from cycling to pilates to running errands. I just want to live in them all the time. The length is perfect too.

When I first received these, I loved the color, style, and feel of them. But by the 2nd use, the bottom seam that connects the mesh panel to the rest of the legging started to come unraveled and was visibly coming apart. I was hoping these leggings would last and hold up, because they indicate they are for "training", but unfortunately that was not the case. I really wanted to love them, but the quality is just not up the Lululemon standard.

column6:

I have trouble with size 4 because they’re too big in the waist So I guess I only get to keep the black pair. If they had pockets they would be perfect

column5: Not as good as last year's model at all
column6: I bought pants with the same name last year that were perfect. They were thin, but not too thin, they had pockets, and most importantly, they stayed up during burpees and squats all workout long. Unfortunately, I only bought 2 pairs. So when I saw these with the same name, I was so excited. Yes, they did not have a pocket. But the rest had to be the same, right? No, no they are not. The fabric is noticeably thicker--enough that I sweat more in them. The fabric is not as soft or as nice. Worst of all, though, they do not stay up. I spend half my workout pulling them up. Even with the cord tied tight. I am keeping them, but I definitely won't buy more of them. I wish they would bring back the ones from last year, I would buy a lot more pairs.

column6: The material is pretty light. I ran in them and never had to pull them up or adjust them. I like the higher rise and flat waistband. The pocket holds my phone, which isn't the case for most tights. The blue print looks like the ocean - gorgeous. I'd definitely buy these again.

My 3rd pair of trains times! Love the prints and fit. Wore daily on my Napa trip as casual wear. Many compliments! I would say that this last pair slight bit longer then previous. Tag says the same 25” in length. But so far love them!
I have had these for about a year and they are still holding up like new. The fabric is soft and stretchy. They fit great. I wear them while at the gym or just around the house. Great pant!

These were the second pair of lulus that I have ever owned and I got them because I had another pair from this brand that I loved. However, after being worn only a few times they began to pill on the inner thigh. I am more on the bigger side so my legs do rub together more but I have not had this problem with any of the other leggings that I have purchased from this brand.

column6: These pants are perfect in every way. They are so durable and holds everything in just right. I've had these for less than a year, and sad to say I am now noticing some wear and tears like pilling and loosening of the material. I wish they would last a little longer. However, I would definitely repurchase this!

I own about 10 pairs of Lulus, and I wear a 4 in every legging except these. They are the perfect combo of slimming/stretch material. I sized down to a 2, because I wanted a little extra compression. The high rise waist also helps so much. If you didnt want the extra squeeze, your true size would provide a more relaxed wear. This material is soft but not too thin. I really recommend this pair. They are the most comfortable of all my "compression" pairs.

These pants look very good on AND they hold up well in workouts! They are tight, but just tight enough to where they stay where they are at and even feel like they help keep it all "sucked in" aka I don't feel like my stomach is bulging out. This is my first time buying the Train Times pant and I will definitely be purchasing more!

I LOVE the train times pant. This is my favorite workout pant. I am only 5’4” so it’s a full length pant on me which I love. The train times pant is comfortable and holds everything in place while I’m working out. My absolute fave!

I wanted to love these so badly after I first tried them on but they are so see through!! I barely bend over and you can see everything so I can't work out in them which is a shame given that I'm not paying this much money to sit around in them!!!! very upset with Lululemon quality I've never had this problem before with the countless other products I've bought from there

column6:
What I love most about this pair is the compression in the right places (read waist), squat proof, the print completely hides sweat, and they stay put throughout the workout. So far I am loving Train Times.
I'd say they are true to size, I purchased my usual size 6 (I'm 5'8, waist 27", 135 lbs). I purchased Train Times before in a size 4 and I feel that the difference between those two sizes is in the waist band, the 4 felt much tighter, legs felt the same.
I feel like these run a little small, but still do-able. They really sucked me in and made my waist look tiny.
I love these leggings. They're really comfortable and have lasted great through washing and drying. I've had them for almost 2 years and they still look new. I am 5'2" 103lbs and size 4 fits snugly.

column5: Favorite leggings out of all lululemon by far!
column6: I have 4 pairs of these now and they do not disappoint (the oldest ones are a year old now). The waistband holds you in super snugly and is super flattering, plus I never have to pull them up when I'm working out! They also look super cute dressed up with a sweater but also look great in the gym.

Train Times has to be one of my favorite running pants ever. They are so soft, the 7/8 length perfect and my favorite. But they are extremely hugging... very tight fit. i don't hate the fit because it sculpts my legs perfectly, but they are not as loose pulling them on.

These are by far the best pants you make. I’ve struggled with the quality of lululemon pants lately. But these are by far the best. Stay in place wonderful pants. I wish they came without the mesh that’s my only dislike.

column6: I have these in grey, and absolutely love them. They are way more durable than aligns and wunderunders. But then I ordered them in the same size in black, and they fit a lot differently. Not as comfortable, and they don't stay up as well. So I'd recommend trying them on in person. If you find a pair that fits right, they're great!

I liked the feel of these tights, but they are way too tight and uncomfortable to do any sort of activity in. I was told these were good for running and I am not a fan of them at all. Disappointed I can't return them.

column6: There’s not 1 thing that I don’t like about these pants - they fit SO well, perfect height for being high waisted, flattering, so comfy, last forever, wear well, can dress them up a little bit, and the stitching is great where it doesn’t go straight across your butt. I wish I had these in every single color because I swear I’d wear them everyday.
The shade of blue was great, the waistband and butt fit sorta odd due to the stitching and waist band, but the shade of navy was perfect.
column11: I KEEP MY AGE ON THE D.L.

column6:
Give yoga pants a whole new look.
I suggest going up one size from normal size.

First I have to say that this pants have quickly become one of my favorites. Great for everything from yoga and cardio. I own 5 pair with the 6th pair on their way via send sale.
Sadly, one pair let me down today. I bought the Hinshu Alpine pattern this spring when it first came out. I have only worn them a few times but today during my cardio class I noticed that I was having to pull them up a lot. They seemed fine until I started bouncing around and then it became a tug fest. Not sure what happened.
Love the mesh detailing and the overall fit but this particular pair just isn't holding up to what you expect from Lulu

column5: Train Times Sweet in the Heat
column6: I love these for a full morning at the gym. I can go from spinning to weights to yoga and they stay in place. I like the adjustable band that helps to keep them snug. The mesh sides help to keep me cool when the hot yoga class gets steamy. The length is perfect. These are sweet!

These are my favorite tights! I have almost every color. I had to return the night view color because for some odd reason they were see through. I also have them in white and they are not see through.

I own a couple of lululemon pants and have rarely had any issues with them. And some of the pants are a few years old and have maintained their quality.
Back in March I bought a pair of these in black and immediately loved them. I loved how flattering they were and how they made me feel pulled in and secure during my workouts. However, after 3 wears the seams in the waist area started coming undone and unraveling. A few weeks later the thread from the seams at the ankle started to unravel as well. I expected way better quality at this price point.
In spite of that I decided to give these another chance. I purchased a pair in Heathered Black. I didn't like the color. It wasn't a flattering color in my opinion so I returned them and ordered them in Dark Olive.
column19: {'LL_response_content': 'Thanks for reaching out and providing this feedback for us.\n\nI\'m sorry to hear you\'re experiencing unraveling seams with your Train Times 7/8 Pant *25". I\'m going to follow this up with an email that outlines how to move towards a resolution.', 'LL_response_date': 'September 20, 2018'}

column6: Love these a bunch I ordered 3 diff colors. They’re excellent for spin class or weight training. I love how tight they are but not too restrictive!

These pants give some compression, and the mesh looks great. I love the drawstring and back pocket stash! Drawstring is important otherwise the pants will fall down. The half hexagon pocket is really good, securely stashes any cards or cash, and the pointy end of the pocket off to the side is good for securely holding my keys!
Very comfortable and smooth. No pilling after 5+ washes, unlike what I've heard about other LL leggings.

column5: Completely ripped the 2nd time I tried them on
column6:
I feel like I must have recieved a defect pair or something, because I'm kind of stunned what just happened now.
I ordered these online, tried them on-LOVED the way they feel/look etc. and couldn't wait to wear them to the gym. The second time I put them on, I'm pulling them up over my hips and I feel a HUGE rip. The entire fabric underneath my butt split wide open. I was shocked. I've NEVER had a pair of lulus or any leggings for that matter do that to me. And before you say "Well, were they too small?" No, they were not. I'm usually a size 2 and I made sure to even size up to a 4 because I knew these could potentially be a little compressing.
I am SO upset, because I know this color and size is completely sold out everywhere. I'm going to take them back today, but I am still so shocked and bummed that this happened.

We'll be reaching out via email, so keep your eyes peeled on your inbox. Chat soon!", 'LL_response_date': 'September 19, 2018'}

column6: Purchased these with a gift card after returning another lulu pair, and I’m more disappointed with these. After three or four wears I noticed multiple loose threads and a small hole in the left thigh. Since then they have continued to pill and there are loose threads along the entire mesh seam. Bummed because I love the fit, but overall not worth the price

column5: BUY THESE PANTS - THE BEST I HAVE EVER OWNED!
column6: I now have two pair of the Train Times pant and am slowly adding to my collection and these pants are AMAZING. I am a spin instructor who teaches 2+ times a week and these pants are on a weekly rotation. After having them for a year, they are still in great condition. The waist band never rolls, the feel secure, and they look great. I love these pants and want them in every color!

I usually only wear Wunder Under, Full-on Luon or Zone In so I was hesitant to buy these. I had never worn mesh before and I worried that it would be itchy. Not only is the mesh so soft and comfortable but the waist band is so amazing!!! There is compression but you don't feel like a stuffed sausage and it never cuts in to the midsection. These are so beautiful and comfortable. I found my new favorite pants. Time to get these in every color!!!

The train time pant is my favorite (squat proof pant) that lululemon has to offer. It hugs my body perfectly and I never have to adjust it while I’m working out. The seams accentuate everything perfectly.

Love the feel of this fabric, the pattern and comfort. While these are full length - I can pull the leg up a bit and wear them just below calf just fine for pseudo Capri look (I have long legs). Because I'm short waisted, normally I stay away from high waisted, but these are fine. And I could make one giant fold and they'd be more like hip huggers. Thrilled w/ the light colored patterns as also serve as my 'white jeans' in summer - awesome traveling pant, look fab and great for workout.
column15: only caution is keeping the side seams and mesh aw

column6: I really want to love these pants, but after wearing them only a couple of times the seams started to fray. It is a real bummer after spending so much money on these tights. Otherwise these pants are great.

column6: I love the hugged feeling these pants provide while I’m training, no extra jiggle!! The fabric is perfection. Love the fun pattern as well!!
Awesome pants that stay put!!

These fit well. I love the compression! They are tough but also feel great while working out. I own the black pair and I love them. I need to snag a few more.
If you want sturdy gym leggings, these are the ones to get.

I was so excited when these leggings arrived because the pattern is beautiful and I LOVE grey & white. column6: This are my new favorite pants. They are body hugging but not to the point where your blood circulation feels like it's been cut off. The small amount of sheer fabric found on the bottom of the pant leg adds a nice unique touch to the garment. I am normally a size four and this remains true for this pant. For reference I am 5'3, 131 lbs.

I am a short girl so when I purchase leggings I need them to be shorter but not cropped. These were the perfect length and are the best material ever. I will never purchase the WonderUnder leggings again these have replaced them.

Love the fact that they have string to prevent the bottoms from slipping or moving during an intense workout. I use these for cardio, gym and during my HIIT workouts. I am a curvy girl, purchased a size 8, and my only issue is that they do not cover cellulite fully maybe it is was because the color I purchased was lighter maybe black would have been my better option. I've gotten many complements on the style and look of the leggings. Love the sheer style at the bottom of the leggings. Not my favorite leggings simply because of the lack of coverage, other than that wearing a long shirt enough to cover my bum would suffice.
This pants have a great fit, along with style. I wear them to spin class and they are great! Please make in more colors and patterns

The lower rise reinforced waistband keeps the pants in place without digging in. The band itself lies completely flat and is smooth yet thick. The length is perfect-doest cut off your leg circulation behind the knee like some crops nor does it bunch at the ankles like some full length pants. It has so much stretch it doesn't bind anywhere making it ideal to wear for all kinds of workouts plus super comfortable to wear all day. I like that the fabric isn't too thin-you can't see through it at all. I have also had super thick pants that it took a small miracle to get on because they were so thick and inflexible. The colors are unique neutrals which is nice if you want to wear as regular clothes

I purchased a pair of the Train Times 7/8 Pant at my local Lulu and loved the way they felt on at the store. When I wore them to my first HIIT class and had no complaints so I ran out and got a second pair. Now I find them falling through the class and im constantly having to pull them back up. I don't think they have stretched out, but I think the issue is when I'm doing a workout where im on the floor then back up like burpees. My first class that I wore them to was about 30 mins on the treadmill, some rowing, and some weights so I didn't experience an issue. Really disappointing because I don't have a way to know what I'll be doing in class that day so I need pants that stay in place through anything. I would recommend these if you're running or lifting weights but sadly thats not be most days so they just sit at the bottom of my drawer

column6: Great pant for running or cycling! Material is durable and won’t chafe. I love the mesh detailing. I’m not a huge fan of drawstring waistbands because they either come loose or you can never untie the knot.

I am an avid Lululemon shopper, and the train times are by far my favorite pants. I have about 7 other pairs, and each color holds true to the high quality and functionality that lulu stands for. The train times have a great high rise waist band that hugs nicely to the tummy, and mesh along the legs that provides great breathability. I am 5’ 3” 125 lbs and the size 2 7/8th pant is right to my ankle. The size 2 is snug, which I prefer, but if you don’t like a very tight athletic pant, I would recommend going one size up. I also love that these pants are great for the gym, or can be dressed up for a casual day look. 10/10 would recommend taking the train times plunge!

I bought these a few months ago in the midnight navy color and have been OBSESSED with them!! The Luxtreme fabric is hands down my favorite material to workout in. The support these leggings give is phenomenal, and I love how breathable the mesh is, its perfect for running. The waistband does not roll down when I'm running and I love the slight compression it gives.

These are my favorite leggings ever!! I bought my first pair to wear for teaching my spin classes and I have never been happier! They are perfect for training and running. They always stay in place and are incredibly flattering. I can not say enough good things about these! Need more colors so I can add them to my collection! They run true to size!

I own over 7 or 8 of these tights... I think that describes pretty well how much I love them. They’re super flattering, comfortable, non-see through ... my oldests one (2 years) have few signs of pilling and they did stretched a little, but they’re still great. I use them for body pump, body combat, cardio hiit, cycling, hiking, in general for all indoor and outdoor activities... btw I always get many compliments.

I’m a big fan of full-on luxtreme, because I love the feeling of being held in / supported when doing HIIT workouts, or leg day, and the fabrication on these tights gives me exactly that. I love how streamlined the design of these are, with a touch of edge (the mesh on the sides), but simple, and the high waist ensures these stay up. These don’t lose their shape, they wash great, and the twine multi white isn’t sheer at all. In the train times, I purchase a size 4, which is what I purchase in the speed up crop/pant & tight stuff tight. If it helps, I’m 24” waist & 33.5” hips, 109lbs. In the nulux, everlux & all the right places, I wear a 2.

column6: These Train Times 7/8 pants are a perfect fit. I wear them for yoga and they stay put perfectly. They also wash well. I wash them inside out and don’t put them in the dryer. Couldn’t be happier! Definitely recommend.

These are my favorite pants for running and lifting! They stay in place, don't slip or ride down and are very flattering and comfortable. I have these in black and then got the sage/olive color where they were on WMTM. I haven't had any quality issues so far.. especially in comparison to the nightmare buying Luon has been since like 2016. Seem to run TTS, if not slightly snug. I'm 5'7, 150 lbs, wear a 6 on tops, 6-8 on bottom. The waistband doesn't have "give" like other luxtreme pants because there is a seam, so keep that in mind if you are in between sizes. There's no way I'd be able to get a 6 over my hips for this reason. But if you are on the fence about purchasing them, I'd give them a whirl. I kind of wish they sold a version without the mesh so they would be a little more versatile #and so I could have both ;# )

Having read some reviews I was hesitant to buy these, especially since I wanted them in white. However, after trying them out and going to a couple of yoga classes... They're awesome.
Remember that heavy, sumptuous, smooth fabric feel from our first Lulus? These babies got it.
10/10 I'd purchase again

I do indoor cycling 5-6 days a week and these are hands down my favorite style of leggings to wear. They stay put with the right amount of compression but are still comfortable and breathable with the mesh. Own several pairs and love them!

The Train Times are a great work out pant. They stay up and hold everything in. The touch of mesh on the calf helps on the hot days in the gym. I enjoy these running, lifting, and yoga. I would recommend sizing down if your are between sizes I was wearing an 8 and they seemed to start to loosen up after running for about 20 mins. so I have started wearing 6s and they continue to hold everything in. I have them in several colors and they all look flattering on. one downfall is there is only one non-zippered pocket on the back. it holds in my cell phone on a run and I like that there is no zipper for floor exercises. however, should you put anything small like an ID or Card in there it may fall out.

I really love the fit when I first wore it that I fell in love. Therefore, I bought the white and black one in crop. For some reason, the seams of the green and black started to come off. I was bummed that it happened. However, I love these pants so much that I want to buy them in other colors. I like how it tight and keeps everything in place and most off it make my bottom perky lol
Like them so much it’s my 2nd pair. Husband bought me a pair of these and the crop version for Mother’s Day. He benefits by me wearing them :)

These are my favorite favorite favorite tights - until this pair! I own 6 pairs of these pants and have never had issues with the patterns I purchased being see-through. Unfortunately this pair was :( hopefully this is not the case for other patterns. For reference I purchased the Shoreline multi-blue. Hopefully this isn't an issue with other patterns because these are my favorite!

column5: Best tights for any activity but beware expansion with long use
column6: I love these tights! The are great for mat classes and cardio alike. Beware using them too often and washing because they will expand with long term use despite costing usd 98.
This particular material seems to be extra stiff and I'd say that the waist runs a size small compared to every other item I own. Not my favorite pair of leggings.

Love that these 7/8 pants are zipper free and have mesh for ventilation! I have these in pants and crops and both versions look very flattering, even on those of us who are short. For reference, I’m 5’1” and wear a size 4.
Can’t complain about these. They stay up when I am running. Most pants I am constantly pulling up. And the burgundy/purple color is perfect
Super flattering.

These leggings are in the running for my favorite pair from lulu. I have them in the white pattern as well as black and love the mesh that adds an extra layer of style and airflow. They are excellent for hot yoga classes because they stay put and are breathable. I would highly recommend!
Love these leggings. I use them for crossfit and never have an issue with them! They stay in place, wick sweat, and go with me everywhere. Love love love them!

I own multiple pairs of the train times pants and they were my favorite until I bought the navy pair. I have had the navy pair for less than 5 months and have maybe washed them five times. I always followed the care instructions and hung them dry, but the last time I washed them a huge hole ripped in the crouch . I loved these pants, but now they are completely unwearable.

column6: Bought these as a summer workout pant, well I should have given them a test run before taking them on vacation because they were so uncomfortable. Had to cut my hikes short which was pretty disappointing. They double the fabric to make the white less transparent but it only makes them very thick and hard to wear.

column6: I love these! Would buy again

These pants are fabulous. I have them in a capri version as well. As a Jazzercise instructor teaching intense cardio/strength classes, these do the best job at sweat wicking. The material is breathable (with the mesh) and they hold me in perfectly.
Shorties be prepared - I am 5'1" and they fit like pants. So there is no 7/8 look when you have short legs!!! I still love the look - they hit right at the ankle on me.

I love these pants! They are wonderful compress pants, don't stretch out, and are great for intense workouts! I had them in the black color at first and then I went out to buy two more. However, both the black and one of my new pairs are starting to go downhill. One pair is starting to almost unravel from the seams, and the other got snags on the front part of the thigh and making it unsightly. None of my luxtreme pants have ever gotten snags on the fabric so it is highly disappointing considering the price. I would love to recommend these to friends and coworkers but I'm so skeptical now.

column6: I got the gravity color, which is like a dark blue grey color. These run a little small due to the Luxtreme material. They are also about 2 inches shorter than my In Movement Pants, which are also 25 inches. Not sure why these are so much shorter, but I still like them!

column5: I should have read the reviews
column6:
I have several train time 7/8 pants and have not had an issue, so I bought them without reading the latest reviews. This was a mistake: this new color is see- through and not up to the standards of the previous versions.
It is strange how a high end lulu tight can have such poor material!

column6:
The train times are one of my favorite bottoms for training and running.
First, I like the fit. The rise is perfect and they “hold you in”.
I buy them in my TTS (4) and they fit on the tighter side so I never need to adjust them while working out. If you don’t like your pant to be tight, I recomend sizing up. They are not as tight as the “tight stuff” but they are not as “giving” as the “fast and free”.
Second, they have mesh, which I like. It adds to the look and to the function!
I also think that the length is great for training.
My only complain is that they don’t have side pockets....
I never liked the back pocket and I’m always reaching out to the pants with the side pockets first...
other than that, they are perfect!

column5: My favorite lululemon style by farrr!
column6:
These tights are honestly the best. Since I'm petite at 5'3" it's hard to find a good pair of full length leggings that aren't too long. I recommend these for those who are more on the athletic side with muscular legs and bum and a smaller waist like myself. They never slide off and they fit my legs like a glove.
I have them in three colors and they have all been wonderful even after continuous wash cycles!
These are great-fitting spectacular pants. A drenching sweat won't loosen the fit.

I had previously bought this style before with no issue. So I ordered another pair on line, needing some new colors to add to my collection. To my surprise these pants were straight up see through. You could see my underwear from the front and the back and I had ordered two different colors. Both colors were the same issue. I was extremely disappointed. Which begs the question, has the material changed? This has never been an issue in the past. If you have bought or are going to buy a pair in the near future, better check them out before you head to the gym.
column19: {'LL_response_content': "Hey NikMarie23,\n\nThanks for taking the time to pass along some feedback on the Train Times 7/8 Pant. We look forward to speaking with you soon!", 'LL_response_date': 'July 22, 2018'}

column6: These are by far my favorite lulu pants. Perfect for any sweat session at the gym! Not to mention they make you look great and feel fabulous! A+ all the way on these! I have several pairs and all look and hold up great after washing and hang dry.

I am honestly surprised by all the negative reviews about this product. I have not experienced any pilling or wear in the seams after owning 2 pairs for over 3 months. I wear and wash mine every week after a heated yoga sculpt class. They are compressive enough where they don't fall down during squats or cardio, but stretchy enough where I can still find my deepest lunge with comfort. Overall, I love everything about these pants! I am 5' 2" and 105lbs with a petite build and the size 4 is PERFECT. I am always a size 4 in "Full on Luxtreme/Luon" pants at lulu, whereas for "Luxtreme/Luon" I am a 2. I am seriously amazed at the fact that I never have to pull my pants up during my workout! These leggings are pricey but worth it!

Bought these pants and have always loved them but recently they have started to peel on the sides and have stretched out from my body. Upset because they used to work so well for me and now they do not preform.
column19: {'LL_response_content': 'Dear Ejoan,\n\nThank you for taking the time to share your feedback with us. I\'m sorry to hear that your Train Times 7/8 Pant *25" is not performing for you! Keep an eye out for an email coming your way. Chat soon!', 'LL_response_date': 'July 19, 2018'}

column6: I wanted to love these leggings. They had compression and were a good length...then I started to work out. I did a jump squat and had someone tell me they could see my underwear. Then, close up, you could see the sweat on my leggings. Enough said.

They are a great pair of crop leggings for me, since I'm 5'11'' and too tall for the actual cropped leggings. The high rise feature is awesome, and I love the thickness of the leggings. Not too thick, but still enough coverage and support to feel comfortable. Highly recommend!

column6: I have absolutely no complaints about these leggings. Never had a problem with the mesh ripping or any seams coming undone. These are lightweight and versatile for any activity. They never sag and I love the cool, smooth feel of the Luxtreme fabric. The best part is nothing sticks to these-- no cat hair, lint, dust, etc! Highly recommended and will be purchasing more!

column6: These are my go-to training tights and are soooo comfortable I forget I have them on. I love the higher rise and compression which is very flattering. Full on luxtreme is my favorite compression fabric. I own 5 pairs and so far they are all 100% squat-proof. The drawcord waistband is definitely a plus and keeps it from sliding down. They do get a bit hot but I think that's what you get for full on luxtreme, which I believe is 2 layers of luxtreme for that compressed feel and coverage. For really hot days I just wear shorts.

Finally found a pair of lululemons that don't slide down and give saggy crotch! They are super-compressive. Which is great for me, but I mean they are tight. So you've been warned. I was a little surprised with how hot I was in them, though. They're think, which make them flattering, but some of my other leggings are the same thickness but don't quite make me sweat so much! Only drawback for now. Hopefully they don't stretch out over time. I've been using them for lifting, movement training, and coaching my athletes. So far so good.

Loves these pants. The high rise stays in place during runs and keeps me cool. Originally bought the black pair and went back for a second pair in a color. 5'7 and 150 pounds - true to size and doesn't change shape. I've worn lululemon for years and these are my new fave pants.
These are a leave-behind item - despite the sale price! These are completely see-through! Tried even with light colored undies and these are a total no-go!

As I wear the train times shorts nearly daily, thought I would try the train times 7/8 pant when I saw the white. I also ordered in Jasmine White Multi/White. The white is lined and so very thick, heavy, uncomfortable and hot. They are very heavy just holding. I am not worried about "see thru". Just needed white for some additional coverup as in Florida, in the sun all the time. Returning. The fabric weight of the Jasmine White Multi/White is similar to the shorts, but not as comfortable as the shorts, feel like they are pulling down. Also, the netting is not comfortable as larger area than the shorts, and netting area so large will not help protect from the sun. Returning.

column6: These pants are nice, similar to all the right places, compression-wise. The drawcord doesn't give you much of a muffin-top, like I thought it might. These pants are great for the gym, which is always a plus. Would recommend!

I recently bought these in the celadon color. The fit and color are great. I'm a runner and had no issues with them staying in place, however, after the first wear, I noticed the side seam is already coming undone. For the price, I would not expect that to happen. I have a number of other Lulu pants some years old and have not had the same issue.

Right away when I got them, I noticed a few seams popping on the ankles but I just ignored it because I loved the pants so much. Sadly, this continues to happen no matter how delicate you care for them. The entire seem in between the legs has come unraveled and I am afraid to wear them in fear that it will rip open while I am at the gym. Would not buy again.

column6: Wore these for many activities including yoga, jogging, burpees and they stay where they are supposed to. I really like the mesh stripe on the side which makes them stylish too. I have washed and dried them a few times with no piling or shrinkage problems.

These pants are described as good for training/boot camp but after four wears at the most-- I have a BIG, NOTICEABLE hole in the thigh. I am so sad about this as I love the fit and feel of these pants. I am a dedicated lululemon customer and this is the first time I have branched out from my aligns. Obviously this fabric is not durable and that is really disappointing. I have never had this type of issue so maybe it was just this certain pair. I would expect a training pant to hold up better than this pair did. I would still recommend this pant to anyone and continue to buy lulu but I am very sad about the hole in my pants.

column6: I love these leggings so much! The fabric is soft and comfortable. I mainly run in them and the hugged sensation make them my favorite to run in. The fabric is thick enough that they aren't see through, which is very important. Overall, they are just the best leggings! I've had them for about a year and they are still are my favorite leggings. They are durable, comfortable, and soft all while looking great!

I have this pair in black-true to size. I love them for running or strength training. I also bought them in jasmine-multi. This pair is hard to pull up over my thighs bc even in the same size the waistband is way to tight and also bending over there is transparency in the back. Once I get them on they feel really nice so I kept the second pair.
Tonight I ordered a couple more pairs to see if I can find more that fit like my black pair. I have high hopes but if they are too tight in the waist they will be returned.

I love my Train Times pants...all though they have the mesh the ventilation isn't the best,they are still very nice pants. They are super cute and can be worn casually or to the gym, and I love how the waist band stays on unlike some of their other leggings...However, when a small hole appeared in mine the patching job totally ruined the look of these pants! But, a new pair is on the way! These are definitely my favorite pair of leggings from Lulu I own!

I've been shopping with Lulu for years, and these are by far my favorite, go to pants. I have several pairs, long and cropped, and have never had one single problem. The high waist and tighter compression keep everything lifted and in place for high intensity workouts and running, and they're flattering on the bootie! The material isn't too thin so I've had no problem with sheerness (although I admittedly don't ever buy white workout pants). Some of my Train Times are over a year old and still look and perform beautifully. I've never had a single issue with stitching or mesh falling apart, and I wash them in the regular cycle with all my other clothes. I'm highly skeptical of the reviews stating their Train Times pants fell apart!! If I could give these pants 10 stars I would!

I really like these leggings! I got them in the light green seafoamy color BUT...I've only worn them 3 times and there are these huge runs in them coming from the crotch area down to the ankle or calf :( I'm super bummed because yes the leggings are not see through....but you can see the runs in them. The same thing happened with my dark green Nulux leggings too :( Why are there so many runs?!

column6: Got these pants a few months ago and have to keep myself from wearing them every time I workout! Love the high rise to hold me in and the simple mesh on the side. Seams are flattering as well. Luxtreme is always great!

I have tried tons of leggings in all sorts of fabrics and fits. These are easily the most versatile leggings. They stay up during bootcamps, metcons, runs, and cycle classes. The material is thick so you are secure, but they are not hot nor trap sweat and moisture. Quick drying and flattering always. I own five pairs. Definitely recommended especially for high intensity workouts that require more structure and support for fast movements.

I ordered these online and when I tried them on I loved the way they hugged my body but was so disappointed when I bent over you could see right through them. The lettering on the tag was visible through the fabric. I'm not sure if sizing up would've made a difference but I exchanged them in store for some Aligns. I would love to try these again in another color but if it's got white in it the fabric needs to be opaque. I expect more out of a $100 pair of leggings.

The train times collection is my absolute favorite for powerlifting. Thank you for creating durable, form fitting and reliable pants! I've had otherwise good experiences with the wunder under and aligns, as my training style does not accommodate with the type of material, but train times keeps me a happy and loyal customer. Can't wait for the next set of colors to come out!

I love these pants. They stay up when running, they don't show sweat, and they are very flattering. I got my usual Lulu size (4), and they fit perfectly. I have worn these 20+ times for Barry's Bootcamp and haven't experienced any pilling, stretching, or discoloration. I love them and will be buying more.

I am so sad to write this review but I don't want anyone else to waste their hard-earned money on the pants. I only wore them a few times and the stitching in the knee started to tear and now there is a hole in the knee. I am so disappointed especially because I washed them exactly as directed and ran in them a few times.

column6: I have two pairs of these and love them! i reecently went down a size in leggings so my 6's are starting to become too big. I ordered a size 4 in the Jasmine White Multi/White and they were sooooo see through. I love this pattern but not impressed with how see through they are. Taking back the 4's. Im not sure if i just need a bigger size or it is the pattern.

I have 4 pairs of these pants now in royal blue, persian blue, navy, and I just bought them in the pattered white pair with the grey stripes. I give these pants 4 stars instead of 5 because the fabric is inconsistent. The solid colors are more silky and thicker than the new patterned pair I just bought which almost feel like the nulu fabric. I still love them either way (I almost prefer the nulu fabric anyways) but it just wasn't what I was expecting.
The other thing: the patterned pair are see through with underwear. This isn't an issue for me because I dont wear any when working out, but if you do watch out! Nude underwear might be the move if you do wear them.

column5: Amazing, some of my favorite lululemons
column6: I got these in the dusty dawn color and fell in LOVE. They're squat proof, stay up, and don't budge throughout any type of workout. The only issue I have is that the material will show almost every sort of panties - you have to wear a thong or one of those no show seam ones. Any sort of lace material will be visible.

At first I was in love with them, the fit is very flattering and overall they have held up well. The biggest downside is they pill very quickly, after about a month of having them areas that you wouldn't even expect to have pilling are very pilled. I have followed all of the washing instructions because they are pricy and I wanted to make sure they would hold up well, unfortunately they have not. There also seems to be some loose strings coming out from the fabric, which has not been able to be remedied. I love the pants, but for the price that they are I would expect better quality especially because they are meant for exercise.

I honestly wasn't expecting to purchase these pants. Long time lulu fan here since 2002 so I've tried and own a lot. I really wanted something in this dusty dawn color and when I turned around and blinked the high waisted wunder unders sold out so I saw these and purchased them in dusty dawn and white. I'm not quite sure where the whole pilling thing is coming from other reviewers but I've never had pilling on anything lulu that was made of luxtreme. Luon well, that's another story but that is the nature of the beast of that fabric no matter what brand. Alo Yoga I'm talking to you. What may pill is the threading but not the fabric and that has happened very rarely. Pretty much only during the whole sheer rear debacle many years ago. I luckily haven't seen a problem since. With that said these appealed to me because at 5' tall I've grown to accept that leggings were never made with us short legged gals in mind. The petite people that can get away with it are size 0 and that I am not. I'm a size 6 in lululemon and everything with long sleeves and full length leggings tend to be too long. These were actually the perfect length and went straight to my ankles. No bunching. I have killer massive calves so they actually fit pretty nice. No open spaces really. I love where these fit on my waist too. High waisted and they hold my stomach in. I like the pocket in the back waist because with a little manipulating I can fit my iphone 7plus in. I like the mesh detail but truth be told I don't LOVE it. I kinda got sick of the whole mesh thing last year. Over all these are freaking amazing. I have to disagree with the negative reviews. I've worn and washed these and I'm lazy people I don't hang dry my stuff. I wash in cold inside out and low air dry in my dryer and they show no wear and tear. I was worried about ordering my true to size in these which is a 6 because the 6 in the speed crop made of the same material is a sausage tight fit. On a good note they hold all of me in on a bad note despite how tight those are I find myself constantly pulling them up. I didn't have that problem with these. Give them a try people. No really give it a try.

I am and always have been a huge fan of all things lululemon until I bought these pants in the mineralize/multi black pattern recently. I didn't realize until my husband pointed it out when we went to the gym together that the print is on top of a white background and anytime i was lunging or stretching, the fabric would stretch out to a white color. At first we thought they were see through but either way it is absolutely unflattering! I am disappointed because they're so cute when they're unstretched but I will definitely think twice before my next purchase of patterned pants. I don't want folks thinking my pants are see through!

column6: Ordered these on sale and I'm very happy with them. I think they are very true to size. I like them especially for extra sweaty gym sessions like running or cycling, but I wear them for anything. Thin enough for all of that, but thick enough that they certainly aren't see-through.

column5: Best weight training pant Lulu makes
column6: These are hands down the absolute best pants lulu makes, and I've tried a lot of fabrics and styles over the years. I currently own 7 pairs of train times, and will continue to add them to my collection. The first pair that I bought a year ago still look new, and have not changed their shape or fit one bit, and I train hard lifting weights in train times every day. Great for leg day, back day, cardio, anything. I don't understand others having issues, because every pair I own is perfect. Also, none are see through, and I own a couple that have white backing. I also have larger, muscular legs. The prints always look perfect. The material is durable and compressive, not thin or cheap at all. No problems with the mesh or seams, which I have experienced with other styles. These are the only pants I've purchased from lulu where I didn't have to use the drawstring cord. Other styles seem to stretch out in the waist, but not these. I recommend them very highly. For reference, I'm 5'3 138 pounds and wear a size 4.

I've worn my pair about 4-5 times now and have followed care instructions, but the seams are starting to fray and there is some slight pilling already. It's a really cute design and the fabric feels durable, but just a few wears to the gym and I have stray strings hanging off of the seams. I still really like them, I just wish they would hold up better for the price.

column6: I initially loved how my train times fit. Snug and comfortable but not too tight. Worn and washed them twice while following care instructions (delicate, cold, air dry) and then pants are now stretched out and big. Found them to be falling down and constantly had to be pulling them back up during workout (third time wearing). I also sized down in hopes to avoid this as I am usually an 8 and ordered a 6.

I look for the perfect pair of pant to teach in. I have used several different versions but that I try on the these and once again I remember why I love them. For me they are perfect for what I teach. I’m on the deck in a pool area of high humidity. We keep it at 86 degrees and water tempts of 86 degree Leadinsweat is truly what I do.
column14: perfect fit for my imperfect body.
column15: love the dark prints more please

column6: Pants fit perfectly at first and then stretched out after two washings (followed care instructions). Pants won't stay up during work out! Will be brining into store and returning. Not the quality I expect from Lululemon.

I have several different kinds of lulus but these are by far my FAVORITE. My training is mostly running and strength work with some hot yoga mixed in. I've worn these pants for all of these workouts and they are excellent for all of those, but they are also great for lounging around or running errands. They are tight but not restricting and they keep you dry and sweat free. They are also very flattering! BONUS: y'all I have two dogs and two cats and pet hair just doesn't stick to these. It's amazing. Some of my other lulus get covered in hair if I just look at my dog from the corner of my eye. I have napped on our fur-covered couch and woke up with no fur anywhere on my pants. Pet owners know how big of a deal this is. I have 3 pairs and will definitely buy more. Also, my oldest pair is a year and a half old (or so) and I wear them all the time and they still look brand new!

column5: great at first but stretched out
column6: These were my favorite leggings when I first got them, they fit great, looked nice and felt amazing. However, after wearing them I noticed they started to stretch out. I made sure to wash them as directed because they were expensive and I didn't want to ruin them, yet they still stretched out. Now they fit a little weird and dont feel supportive or flattering. At first they were perfect and I loved everything about them but just wearing them, as you are supposed to do with clothes, caused them to stretch out and it's no longer worth the price tag.
